Package: terminux
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Terminux Team <desalegnfitsum116-art@example.com>
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31), libx11-6, libwayland-client0 (>= 1.18), libegl1, libxkbcommon0, libfontconfig1, libfreetype6, libxcb1, libxrender1, libxfixes3, libxext6
Recommends: libdbus-1-3, libpulse0, libnotify4
Provides: x-terminal-emulator
Section: x11
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/desalegnfitsum116-art/Terminux
Description: GPU Accelerated Terminal Emulator — Fork of WezTerm
 Terminux is a GPU-accelerated cross-platform terminal emulator and
 multiplexer, forked from WezTerm. It provides a modern terminal
 experience with support for fonts, ligatures, color schemes, GPU
 acceleration, session persistence, plugins, workspaces, and SSH.
 .
 Key features:
  * GPU-accelerated rendering via OpenGL/EGL/Vulkan
  * Lua-based configuration
  * Tab and pane management with split layouts
  * Session persistence with crash recovery
  * Workspace snapshots
  * Plugin system
  * SSH client with mux support
  * Command palette
  * Dark and light themes
